messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/config/paypal

All methods allowed?
- allMethods: false

Individual methods acceptable (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- The route is registered in server.js with:
  app.get('/api/config/paypal', (req, res) => res.send({ clientId: process.env.PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID }));
  This explicitly defines a GET handler for the path /api/config/paypal.
- No other route registration (app.post, app.put, etc.) for this path exists in the provided code, so only GET is explicitly handled.
- The app has general middlewares and a notFound/errorHandler after routes; requests using methods other than GET that reach this path will fall through to those handlers (i.e., there is no explicit handling for them in the code shown).
- Although some frameworks/platforms may implicitly handle HEAD by reusing GET handlers, the prompt requires determination strictly from the code rather than such assumptions; therefore HEAD is marked false.
